# Watched movies



Watched state is separate from removing movies from `movieDatabase`.



## Source file



`app/watched-movies.js` exports:



```javascript

window.watchedMovieListings = [ /* "Title (Year)" strings */ ];

```



Edit this file to persist watched listings across sessions.



## Runtime behavior



- `initWatchedMovies()` (~line 368) loads listings into `watchedMovieSet` on startup

- "Mark watched" on the result card adds to the in-memory set without auto-saving the file

- The Watched Flicks panel lets the user export an updated `watched-movies.js` download

- "Include watched" checkbox controls whether watched movies appear in spin/shuffle/coin pools



## Adding vs removing from catalog



| Action | Where |

|--------|-------|

| Mark as watched (still in wheel if included) | `watched-movies.js` or Mark Watched UI |

| Remove from wheel entirely | Delete from `movieDatabase` in `main.js` (Ticket Stubs prompt) |



Do not confuse the two — watched is a filter flag, not a database deletion.
